main event: Two airmen reported seeing fireballs in the sky on multiple occasions in February 1950.
interesting points: The fireballs were described as being twice the size of the evening star., The objects were seen moving from SSE to E., The sightings were reported at different times, with the last report at 1355 MST., No actual photographs were taken, but sketches were mentioned., The object was not directly seen by the investigators, only by the ground witnesses.
location: Unknown City, Unknown Region, Unknown Country
witness description: airmen who saw the object from the ground
